entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: people who are chicken heads they get their nose in other people is business even if they are just strangers you expect that from a family member or or a friend but you know

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see what you mean

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: especially with the internet that feeds a lot of that now we know what orwell was referring to when he spoke of big brother in nineteen eighty four

entries.text: i do not do much much different than i would otherwise

entries.text: and i have had many temper outbursts

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i kinda argue with my aunt and it was because she was basically making leading statements trying to trap me into saying something about a relative and it annoyed me greatly

entries.text: how close are you to your family

entries.text: i am kind of on the outs with my parents

entries.text: why

entries.text: i am kind of the black sheep

entries.text: it was when i could afford to travel

entries.text: no

entries.text: no

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was diagnosed with depression after a hospital visit in april of two thousand eleven and i took some lexapro but i stopped after one day i did not wanna do it anymore

entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because i did not feel it was helpful i feel i was becoming a zombie

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sucks

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: depressed about not having a job for over two years i lost my job in october two thousand and ten and except for day you know jobs like this which i am fortunate to get just you know daily things focus groups like that i have not worked

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry to hear that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: thank you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: especially when you are fifty six years old

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well eh just it just the i guess the general feeling of hopelessness

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i get out on my bicycle a lot and walk or bike just four hours a day split about two hours each

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah good to get some

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: very easy cause now i am old when i was young i could not sleep more than six four six hours a night

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because i am restless

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no but now that i am old i i i sleep much more easily

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i pray before i go to sleep and that is that is that is when i can not have any trouble sleeping i just pray recite different prayers like the lord is prayer hail mary stuff like that and i am able to fall off to sleep
